  42:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** 
  43:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** /**
  44:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * @ingroup groupTransforms
  45:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** */
  46:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** 
  47:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** /**
  48:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * @defgroup ComplexFFT Complex FFT Functions
  49:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *
  50:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  51:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) is an efficient algorithm for computing the
  52:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT).  The FFT can be orders of magnitude faster
  53:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * than the DFT, especially for long lengths.
  54:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The algorithms described in this section
  55:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * operate on complex data.  A separate set of functions is devoted to handling
  56:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * of real sequences.
  57:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  58:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * There are separate algorithms for handling floating-point, Q15, and Q31 data
  59:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * types.  The algorithms available for each data type are described next.
  60:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  61:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The FFT functions operate in-place.  That is, the array holding the input data
  62:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * will also be used to hold the corresponding result.  The input data is complex
  63:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * and contains <code>2*fftLen</code> interleaved values as shown below.
  64:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * <pre> {real[0], imag[0], real[1], imag[1],..} </pre>
  65:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The FFT result will be contained in the same array and the frequency domain
  66:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * values will have the same interleaving.
  67:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *
  68:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par Floating-point
  69:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The floating-point complex FFT uses a mixed-radix algorithm.  Multiple radix-8
  70:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * stages are performed along with a single radix-2 or radix-4 stage, as needed.
  71:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The algorithm supports lengths of [16, 32, 64, ..., 4096] and each length uses
  72:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * a different twiddle factor table.
  73:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  74:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The function uses the standard FFT definition and output values may grow by a
  75:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * factor of <code>fftLen</code> when computing the forward transform.  The
  76:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * inverse transform includes a scale of <code>1/fftLen</code> as part of the
  77:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * calculation and this matches the textbook definition of the inverse FFT.
  78:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  79:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * Pre-initialized data structures containing twiddle factors and bit reversal
  80:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * tables are provided and defined in <code>arm_const_structs.h</code>.  Include
  81:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * this header in your function and then pass one of the constant structures as
  82:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * an argument to arm_cfft_f32.  For example:
  83:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  84:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * <code>arm_cfft_f32(arm_cfft_sR_f32_len64, pSrc, 1, 1)</code>
  85:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  86:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * computes a 64-point inverse complex FFT including bit reversal.
ARM GAS  /var/folders/6_/psd2b8g56p7696hhrr4ztjs00000gn/T//ccufD371.s 			page 3


  87:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The data structures are treated as constant data and not modified during the
  88:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * calculation.  The same data structure can be reused for multiple transforms
  89:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * including mixing forward and inverse transforms.
  90:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  91:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * Earlier releases of the library provided separate radix-2 and radix-4
  92:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * algorithms that operated on floating-point data.  These functions are still
  93:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * provided but are deprecated.  The older functions are slower and less general
  94:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * than the new functions.
  95:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
  96:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * An example of initialization of the constants for the arm_cfft_f32 function follows:
  97:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \code
  98:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * const static arm_cfft_instance_f32 *S;
  99:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * ...
 100:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *   switch (length) {
 101:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 16:
 102:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len16;
 103:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 104:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 32:
 105:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len32;
 106:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 107:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 64:
 108:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len64;
 109:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 110:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 128:
 111:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len128;
 112:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 113:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 256:
 114:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len256;
 115:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 116:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 512:
 117:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len512;
 118:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 119:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 1024:
 120:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len1024;
 121:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 122:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 2048:
 123:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len2048;
 124:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 125:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 4096:
 126:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_f32_len4096;
 127:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       break;
 128:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *   }
 129:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \endcode
 130:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par Q15 and Q31
 131:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The floating-point complex FFT uses a mixed-radix algorithm.  Multiple radix-4
 132:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * stages are performed along with a single radix-2 stage, as needed.
 133:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The algorithm supports lengths of [16, 32, 64, ..., 4096] and each length uses
 134:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * a different twiddle factor table.
 135:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 136:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The function uses the standard FFT definition and output values may grow by a
 137:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * factor of <code>fftLen</code> when computing the forward transform.  The
 138:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * inverse transform includes a scale of <code>1/fftLen</code> as part of the
 139:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * calculation and this matches the textbook definition of the inverse FFT.
 140:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 141:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * Pre-initialized data structures containing twiddle factors and bit reversal
 142:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * tables are provided and defined in <code>arm_const_structs.h</code>.  Include
 143:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * this header in your function and then pass one of the constant structures as
ARM GAS  /var/folders/6_/psd2b8g56p7696hhrr4ztjs00000gn/T//ccufD371.s 			page 4


 144:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * an argument to arm_cfft_q31.  For example:
 145:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 146:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * <code>arm_cfft_q31(arm_cfft_sR_q31_len64, pSrc, 1, 1)</code>
 147:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 148:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * computes a 64-point inverse complex FFT including bit reversal.
 149:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * The data structures are treated as constant data and not modified during the
 150:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * calculation.  The same data structure can be reused for multiple transforms
 151:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * including mixing forward and inverse transforms.
 152:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 153:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * Earlier releases of the library provided separate radix-2 and radix-4
 154:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * algorithms that operated on floating-point data.  These functions are still
 155:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * provided but are deprecated.  The older functions are slower and less general
 156:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * than the new functions.
 157:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \par
 158:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * An example of initialization of the constants for the arm_cfft_q31 function follows:
 159:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * \code
 160:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * const static arm_cfft_instance_q31 *S;
 161:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** * ...
 162:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *   switch (length) {
 163:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *     case 16:
 164:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_cfft_f32.c **** *       S = &arm_cfft_sR_q31_len16;
